article.description: Richie Adubato had to wait a lot longer than he expected to get his 100th WNBA victory.
article.headline: New York stops six-game losing streak
article.linkText: Liberty beat West-leading Storm, end record skid
article.story:
SPOKANE, Wash. (AP) -- New York Liberty coach Richie Adubato had
to wait a lot longer than he expected to get his 100th WNBA
victory.

Becky Hammon scored 15 points to help the New York Liberty snap
a franchise-record six-game losing streak with a 67-62 victory over
the Seattle Storm on Saturday night.

"It feels to get the 100th win and it feels good to get the
losing string out of the way," Adubato said. "We've lost six in a
row, so I've been looking for this one for quite a while."

Elena Baranova added 13 points for the Liberty (7-7).

Kamila Vodichkova scored 15 points for the Western
Conference-leading Storm (8-4), and Lauren Jackson and Betty Lennox
each had 12 points.

"That's a good Seattle team," said Adubato, a former NBA head
coach. "We gambled on playing a zone, and we gambled on going big.
The last time we played them they outrebounded us 44-26. Tonight we
got the boards, 32-24."

Seattle has lost two straight following a franchise-best
six-game winning streak.

"It's a tough loss, no doubt," Seattle coach Anne Donovan
said. "It's tough to win when they take away the things we do
well. They took away our transition game and they took away our
ability to get the ball inside to Lauren."
